# Devbench / ConfigForge

> Nine essential developer tools + **ConfigForge** — a multi-format config file converter supporting **11 formats** (JSON, YAML, TOML, XML, CSV, INI, .env, HCL, .properties, plist, JSONC). All offline, all private. The yq/dasel alternative with TOML write support.

## Install

```bash
# pip (PyPI)
pip install devbench

# Homebrew (macOS/Linux)
brew tap apeters247/devbench
brew install devbench

# From source
git clone https://github.com/apeters247/devbench && cd devbench && pip install -e .
```

## Quick Start

```bash
# Convert YAML to JSON
devbench cf config.yaml -t json

# Convert JSON to TOML (pipe)
cat package.json | devbench cf -t toml

# In-place edit
devbench cf config.yaml --set server.port 8080 --in-place

# Get a value
devbench cf config.yaml --get server.port

# Dotted key names (e.g. Kubernetes annotations)
devbench cf k8s.yaml --get 'ingressAnnotations.cert-manager\.io/cluster-issuer'

# Batch convert
devbench cf '*.yaml' -t json --batch --output-dir out/

# Merge defaults without overwriting existing keys
devbench cf prod.yaml --merge defaults.yaml --merge-new-only

# YAML 1.2 strict booleans (prevent Norway problem)
devbench cf config.yaml -t json --yaml12

# Show 9 developer tools (token counter, base64, hash, UUID, diff, etc.)
devbench tools
```

## Features

### ConfigForge (`devbench cf`)

Convert config files between any of 11 formats — bidirectionally, offline, with comment preservation.

**Why ConfigForge over yq/dasel?**

| Feature | ConfigForge | yq | dasel |
|---------|-------------|-----|-------|
| TOML write | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| Comment preservation | ✅ Full | Partial | ❌ |
| Formats | 11 | 7 | 8 |
| Dotted key escape (`\.`) | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| Batch/streaming | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| YAML 1.2 strict booleans | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| plist support | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| `pip install` | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |

### Developer Tools (`devbench tools`)

| Tool | Command | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| ConfigForge | `devbench cf` | 11-format config converter |
| JSON | `devbench json` | Format, validate, minify JSON |
| Base64 | `devbench base64` | Encode/decode |
| Hash | `devbench hash` | MD5, SHA-1/256/512 |
| URL | `devbench url` | URL encode/decode + query parsing |
| Timestamp | `devbench timestamp` | Unix ↔ human date conversion |
| UUID | `devbench uuid` | Generate v4 UUIDs (batch supported) |
| Diff | `devbench diff` | Side-by-side text comparison |
| JWT | `devbench jwt` | Decode JWT tokens |

### Supported Formats

| Format | Read | Write | Comment Preservation |
|--------|------|-------|---------------------|
| JSON | ✅ | ✅ | N/A |
| JSONC | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| YAML | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |
| TOML | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |
| XML | ✅ | ✅ | ⚠️ Structural |
| CSV | ✅ | ✅ | N/A |
| INI | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |
| .env | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |
| HCL | ✅ | ✅ | ⚠️ Limited |
| .properties | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ Full round-trip |
| plist | ✅ | ✅ | N/A |

