## Project Structure

```
devbench/
├── core/                   # Main package
│   ├── configforge.py      # 11-format converter engine
│   ├── cli.py              # CLI entry point (devbench command)
│   ├── tools.py            # 9 developer utilities
│   ├── detector.py         # Format auto-detection
│   └── models.py           # Data models
├── tests/                  # pytest suite (1338 tests)
├── web/                    # Landing page + license server
├── homebrew-tap/           # Homebrew formula (brew tap apeters247/devbench)
├── forge/                  # AI agent workspace + SEO pages
└── pyproject.toml          # Build config
```

## Architecture

ConfigForge uses a **line-mapped comment preservation model**: comments are extracted from source text via regex *before* parsing, stored as a linear sequence of line-attached annotations, and re-inserted *after* serialization. This avoids the node-attached comment model used by most YAML libraries, which repeatedly loses or misplaces comments during transformations.

